, advertising them to the industry, to their employees, and to the public at large. If we want to know how studios work-how studios think-we need to watch their films closely. How closely? Maniacally so. In a wide range of examples, The Studios after the Studios explores the gaps between story and backstory in order to excavate the hidden history of Hollywood's second great studio era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aMotion picture industryzCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistory. 0aMotion picture studioszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistory. 4aHollywood. 4aJaws (film). 4aParamount. 4ahigh concept. 4amedia conglomerates. 4astudios. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070398640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804794749zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804794749423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804794749.jpg  a978-3-11-070398-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles